      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JUMBUK WANG WANG (1) struggled in tougher grade last start at Warragul, but prior to that won easily by 4 lengths at this track (24.68) beating Dr. Tessa in a Bottom Up - Grade 6 on March 18. Has ability and is a key runner. DR. AXEL (5) finds it hard to win but looks close to breaking through. Has finished in the placings two on end now, the latest when third (24.76) at this track. Expected to be in this for a long way. SPRING LAVER (6) chased the lead early from the inside and boxed on well to finish third, beaten 4 lengths (22.09) at Shepparton in a Grade 5 over 390m. The form from his last run is stacking up nicely. Can measure up. BRUCE (2) must be included in calculations.",
